      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 695: The pre-Android R crop region assumes SENSOR_INFO_ACTIVE_ARRAY_SIZE starts at (0,0). Some devices report an active array with non-zero left/top offsets, so this crop can be shifted and produce incorrect zoom framing. Build the crop rectangle relative to the active array origin.\n\n```suggestion\n                val left \u003d active.left + (active.width() - w) / 2\n                val top \u003d active.top + (active.height() - h) / 2\n                builder.set(CaptureRequest.SCALER_CROP_REGION, Rect(left, top, left + w, top + h))\n```",
