      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 135: The reset path does not cancel an active long-press progressive zoom animator. If pinch-to-zoom is disabled while the animator is running, the helper is dropped but the animator still holds the TextureView reference and continues calling setTransform(), re-applying zoom after reset and potentially leaking the view. Cancel the animator before resetting state.\n\n```suggestion\n    fun reset() {\n        stopProgressiveZoom()\n        scale \u003d 1f\n        translateX \u003d 0f\n        translateY \u003d 0f\n        apply()\n    }\n```",
